Carders, as it is easy to understand from the name, are people, who illegally access other people’s credit cards and perform operations from the behalf of the cardholder. The worst point for the cardholder is that he does not know he is about to get robbed. Carders might even wait for a bigger sum to land on the card account, before they cash it out.
The main ways carders receive the transactional information are:

 Skimming

Which is scanning credit cards with portable devices.
• Phishing, which is creating fake versions of popular websites. Phishing websites usually use domains that are very similar to popular domains, in order to lure people, who might not notice the mistake in domain
• Key logging. This is a hacking attack, which involves recording user’s actions with his PC. Hackers gain access to the passwords for different websites of a particular user, his or her credit card data and tons of other personal information.
• Using memory tracking malware. This method also involves hacking. Hackers set up their malware on the memory of the payment processor

Using exploits

This method is about analyzing the weaknesses of the security systems of the websites .  Using these weaknesses to gain access to personal information of users . including their credit or debit card numbers, PIN’s and even SSN’s.
After criminals gain access to such information, they either resell it to other parties, or steal the money themselves.  Nowadays, in other countries cards are getting more and more popular, creating new space of operation for criminals.
